{
  "name": "Midnight Tears (Ingested)",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A creature that ingests this &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} suffers no effect until the stroke of midnight. If the &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} has not been neutralized before then, the creature must succeed on a [[/save con 17 format=long]], taking 31 (9d6) &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>Ingested.</strong> A creature must swallow an entire dose of ingested &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} to suffer its effects. The dose can be delivered in food or a liquid. You may decide that a partial dose has a reduced effect, such as allowing advantage on the saving throw or dealing only half damage on a failed save.</p>\n</div>",
